# Change Checklist

agent-messenger has features, shortcuts, defaults, and identity examples duplicated across many files. When changing ANY of the following, you MUST update ALL listed locations or the codebase becomes inconsistent.

## Shortcuts / Commands (#help, /am)

If you add, rename, or remove a shortcut:

1. `README.md` — Shortcuts table
2. `docs/setup-guide.md` — Shortcuts table
3. `.cursor/rules/agent-messenger.mdc` — Shortcuts list (Cursor `#` commands)
4. `src/cli/init.ts` — Embedded `CURSOR_RULE` string AND the matching `SKILLS` entry
5. `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` — Live CC skill file (if it exists in this repo's working copy)

## Identity / Agent Defaults

If you change default agent IDs, identity examples, or session ID formats:

1. `README.md` — Identity & Multi-Agent section, diagram
2. `docs/setup-guide.md` — Identity section, init options table
3. `docs/development.md` — Manual MCP Configuration examples, --env docs
4. `.cursor/rules/agent-messenger.mdc` — Identity section
5. `src/cli/init.ts` — `parseArgs` defaults, `CURSOR_RULE` identity section, relevant `SKILLS` entries (especially `/sm`)
6. `src/cli/index.ts` — CLI help text (init options)
7. `.claude/skills/sm/SKILL.md` — Default send target
8. Tests — `tests/cli.test.ts` (checks help output defaults)

## Supported Agents / Environments

If you add or change supported agent environments (--env values, auto-detection):

1. `src/config.ts` — `AgentEnv` type, `detectEnv()` function
2. `README.md` — Opening line, diagram, Identity section
3. `docs/setup-guide.md` — Opening line, identity section
4. `docs/development.md` — `--env` flag documentation
5. `src/tools/send-message.ts` — Schema description (agent examples)

## Version Bumps

If you change the version number:

1. `package.json` — `version` field
2. `src/index.ts` — McpServer version string

## Workflow Tools

If you add, rename, or remove workflow tools:

1. `src/index.ts` — Tool registration
2. `docs/development.md` — MCP Tool Parameters section
3. `README.md` — Shortcuts table (if it has a shortcut)
4. `docs/setup-guide.md` — Shortcuts table, workflow section
5. `.cursor/rules/agent-messenger.mdc` — Shortcuts list
6. `src/cli/init.ts` — `CURSOR_RULE` shortcuts, `SKILLS` entries

## How to Use This

Before marking any feature/docs PR as complete, grep for the old values across the full codebase:

```bash
rg "old-value" --type ts --type md
```

If matches remain in any of the listed locations, update them.
